<TITLE> New BDR chief takes office </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 10 (bdnews24.com)  Major General Rafiqul Islam has taken office as the head of the Bangladesh Rifles, replacing Major General Mainul Islam. A press release signed on Monday by BDR public relations officer Mohammad Mohsin Reza confirmed the takeover. Major Rafiqul was the head of the auxiliary force, Bangladesh Ansar and Village Defence Force. The new BDR chief completed his army staff course from Kuala Lumpur Armed Force College in Malaysia in 1987. He was appointed the deputy regional commander of United Nations Peacekeeping Mission (ONUMOG) in Mozambique between 1993 and 1994. He was commissioned to the Bangladesh Army's Signals Corps on Nov 30, 1976.
